lines.text: HEMOGLOBIN A1C (HEMOGLOBIN A1C, SCREENING OR PREDIABETIC MONITORING) - Final result (08/26/2015
A repeatable Hb Alc > or = 6.5% is diagnostic of diabetes. A single Hb Alc >
or = 6.5% can also be confirmed by a fasting plasma glucose measurement > 125
mg/dl, a random plasma glucose > or = 200 mg/dl, or a 2 hour oral glucose
tolerance test result > or = 200 mg/dl. Patients with Hb Alc of 5.7-6.4% are
at increased risk for future diabetes.
